import json import java.io from org.apache.commons.io import IOUtils from java.nio.charset import StandardCharsets from org.apache.nifi.processor.io import StreamCallback
class ModJSON(StreamCallback): def __init__(self): self.ks = '' pass def process(self, inputStream, outputStream): text = IOUtils.toString(inputStream, StandardCharsets.UTF_8) text = text.replace(' -','Temp0raryChang3-') newObj = '' # split around semicolon and then strip spaces from the ends fieldPair = map(lambda s: s.strip(), text.split(' ')) newObj+=str("{"); for i in range(len(fieldPair)): aPair = map(lambda p: p.strip(), fieldPair[i].split(':',1)) newObj+=str('"'+aPair[0]+'":'+aPair[1].decode('string_escape').replace('Temp0raryChang3-',' -')+",") self.ks+=str(aPair[0]+"\n")
newObj = newObj.rstrip(',') self.ks = self.ks.rstrip('\n') newObj+=str("}") newObj = newObj.replace('Temp0raryChang3-',' -') bytes = bytearray(newObj.encode('utf-8')) outputStream.write(bytes) # outputStream.write(bytearray(json.dumps(newObj, indent=4).encode('utf-8')))
flowFile = session.get() if (flowFile != None): modjson = ModJSON() flowFile = session.write(flowFile, modjson) flowFile = session.putAttribute(flowFile, "filename", flowFile.getAttribute('filename').split('.')[0]+'_translated.json') flowFile = session.putAttribute(flowFile, "field_keys", modjson.ks) session.transfer(flowFile, REL_SUCCESS) session.commit()
